{
  "stem": "13469.5",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The main thing from my point of view, being privileged in Belsen-- and-- and-- and we do recognize, now, that we did have a privileged existence in Belsen, compared with many other people who I've met after the war, and who are survivors who were in Belsen-- especially those who came from Auschwitz-- who had a far harder time than we had in Belsen.",
      "word_count": 64
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But we were privileged.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But nevertheless, it wasn't exactly a holiday.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But we were allowed to keep our own clothes, for example.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we had our own clothes with the yellow star on it-- so that was obviously a lot better than the Auschwitz women who were all in their striped, zebra uniforms, pajamas.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, we could take all our possessions from Westerbork with us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we have other clothes, and we had books, and I believe many of the Orthodox Jews had Sefer Torahs and Megillahs and all sorts of praying equipment, and everything.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they practiced all those sort of things whenever they could in Belsen.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We saw that, and that's really the first time, I should think, that we saw these kind of habits, and learned about them and heard them praying, and-- and began to understand it all, really, and copy it, I think.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I suppose it was an education for us.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I think we did it, as well.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When everybody else did it, we did it, as well.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I think sort of there were benefits of being at Belsen.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Basically, in a typical day in Belsen, that the first thing that happened in the morning was the appel, which is basically the roll call.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
